calendar: I synchronize my calendar autonomously with your phone calendar and all calendars that are synchronized to your phone. With this, you have all your appointments and planned activities here with me. I can also learn, how busy you are at different times, when you are busy with what, and I can suggest suitable times for new appointments. In addition, I try to learn not to disturb you during important meetings.
Congrats, you made it through the whole: Congrats, you made it through the whole tutorial! I hope I was able to show you what I want to learn and do for you. Of course, my functionalities will continuously be improved and new ones will be added as well, so that I can support you even more in the future! It would be amazing if you could give as much feedback as possible (on the 'Settings' page). Whatever you need or want, please provide feedback. Okay, enough words, you are ready and I hope I can help you achieve your goals and dreams. Let's go!

You can assign these thoughts to projects directly as thoughts. thoughts: Hi and welcome on the 'Organize' page. Often people remember things that need to be done or should not be forgotten, but they don't have time to deal with it and therefore forget it later. This happens to me on a daily basis.
thoughtsAdd: To avoid forgetting these things, you can open me and save a thought within 5 seconds only. Like this, you can deal with it later when you have time. Here you can see all your saved thoughts and add new ones by clicking on the big '+' icon. With me, you'll never forget anything again!
thoughtsProcess: Save all your thoughts during the day, tomorrow evening we will process them to new todos together. Again, you can click on 'Next' if you want to have a look at it earlier. I'm looking forward to it.

tutorialCalendarPush: Hey, am I annoying you already? Today, I would have a look on the calendar with you as the last part of the tutorial. Open me and visit the 'Calendar' page to start the tutorial.
tutorialNextButton: You made it through the first part of the tutorial, congrats! I will show you further functinalities of mine and what I can learn and will do for you in the coming 3 days step by step. If you want to proceed earlier, just click on the 'Next' button on the top. Also very important: I want to continuously learn and improve. Therefore, if you notive anything that you don't like or is missing, please tell my developers. Under 'Settings' you can provide feedback anytime, please give us as much feedback as possible.
tutorialProjectsPush: Hey, it's me again. Are you ready for the second last part of the tutorial? Open me and visit the 'View' page to have a look on the grouping of todos into projects with me.
tutorialThoughtprocessingPush: Hey, it's me again. You really do have interesting thoughts. Joke, we take data privacy very seriously and nobody will ever read your data. Only I will learn from your data to better support you, if you allow me that. Visit the 'Organize' page to have a look on processing your thoughts.
tutorialThoughtsPush: You are curious, nice. I want to additionally challenge you while working on your first todos: Use me to write down any thought on the 'Organize' page that comes up tomorrow during the day and that you don't want to forget. Tomorrow in the evening we will process your thoughts to new todos together. You can change to the 'Organize' page on the bottom.

tutorialTodoPageInit: You unlocked the 'Do' page, where you can work off your todos. I will directly suggest a todo on this page which you then can start or skip, if you'd like a new suggestion. Additionally, I will learn from every interaction with you, e.g. when you click on 'Skip', I can learn that my suggestion was not optimal. With this, I will try to always find the optimally doable and most important todo for you.
tutorialTodoPageTime: From now on, you can also input your current available time and I will adapt my suggestion to you.
processInit: We took a shortcut to define the first couple of todos. To better learn which todos can and should be worked on when, you need to define your todos with some more detail from now on.
